The All Progressives Congress (APC) has released a revised timetable and schedule of activities for the conduct of the 2022 Governorship Primary Election in Ekiti State. The APC has equally fixed January 27, 2022 for the conduct of the Governorship Primary Election in the state. This was in accordance with provisions of the Electoral Act 2010 (as amended) and Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) guidelines, This was contained in the partyâ€™s official notice issued by the National Secretary of the APC Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC), Sen. John James Akpanudodehe. INEC has fixed June 18, 2022 for the Ekiti governorship election.